    {
      "id": "87f05445b03fb8c2d3e094825f1012d84772a74f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-17 16:28:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI don't understand this change. The only way that destroy_in_progress can be cleared is if done other thread has raced and gone the orphan cleanup already. This can happen in rare cases if one precreate thread is taking a long time to complete, and the MDS sends another precreate request and they are both trying to do the same thing. \n\nThe only purpose for this flag is to detect if the orphan cleanup thread was blocked on fo_create_lock, so if it is ignore in filter_destroy_precreated() then there would be no point in having it at all. \n\nMaybe Mike recalls if there is some other bug in this code?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "97886e723a010d08842b8d0885342ebdebc4add2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-02-18 02:13:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThe point of fo_destroy_in_progress is to abort inflight precreate, thus orphan cleanup thread can get fo_create_lock to start orphan cleanup asap.\r\n\r\nAs I mentioned in LU-2823, in mds failover case, if a orphan cleanup for original mds can't finish before the failover done, the new orphan cleanup for the failover mds will be skipped and the failover mds will have wrong last_id at the end.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "5b24b5ef8481b3d043c1c973b17d9a5efe27c9dc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 118,
        "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
        "email": "mpershin@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "tappro"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-25 06:18:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI don't remember bugs related to that, but tend to agree that at least this is safe to continue with orphan recovery. But I'd add more checks for that case to see does that help or not. Say, if fo_destroy_in_progress is cleared then output not just warning message but also how many orphans we will found after that. That would prove assumption that this is the reason.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "cb4062e0d39d2a9f4f7129a8d719f6e916e6dca2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-02-27 03:19:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nMike, we do have another warning message with lot of information (going to delete from xx to xx, current last is xx) just followed this one, is it enough? What other specific information do you want?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
